			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Quad kiting is mainly done by druids/wizards/rangers ( though easier with dru/wiz )
<br />

<br />
Essentially with a druid/wiz  you pull 4 mobs with snare and land a Point blank targeted area  Effect ( i.e. you target the mob and all mobs in close proximity of that mob you have targeted will get hit )
<br />

<br />
the ae's usually only hit a maximum of 4 mobs.  
<br />

<br />
for a necro its similar but not as easy,   druid/ranger snare lasts 15mins , necros last 2 1/2 mins or something like that we do similar method except for we slap dots on the mobs  instead of using area of effect spells ( we only get like 1 anyways and it sucks )
<br />

<br />
quad kiting imo isnt a real viable option as our mana per spell is pretty high,  easier to just kite one mob at a time and less hassle trying to remember how long snare is gonna last before it wares off on one of the other mobs <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" />.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1014810" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://www3.telus.net/cbriere1/rootedxsig.jpg" border="0" /></a>
<br />
Prexus  - to lazy to change the sig. <img src="images/smiles/icon_razz.gif" alt="Razz" border="0" /></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
