			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I wouldn't call it a major peeve.  I like aggro kiting a lot more than fear kiting.  When you are aggro kiting, YOU control generally where the mob goes.  Sometimes pathing is a little screwy and sometimes stuff warps right on top of you.  You just have to figure out when this is good or when it's bad, because warping is sometimes a good thing.  When fear kiting, you need to know where the mob is going to path when you cast fear on it.  Also you need to worry about fear resists.  Etiher way has it's pros and cons like everything else.  It all depends on your situation.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
