			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The reason it's called quad kiting is that some spells and songs are coded so that only a maximum of 4 things in the Area Effect (AE) can be affected by the AE. For example a wizards snare will snare a MAXIMUM of 4 targets, one of which might be yourself if you're too close to your target. To effectively quad kite you want mobs to run the same speed and have the same hp and not pick up any other mobs while you're kiting.
<br />

<br />
Necro's have no spells that have the 4 mob limit placed on them. The only AE's necro's get are "Word of Spirit"  at level 24 and "Word of Souls" at level 39. They are only really effective when you're in an AE group (everyone in the group is using AE stuns/nukes/dots) pulling 10 or more mobs at the same time.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=490383" target="_blank" class="postlink">Kelter Skelter
<br />
da neckRomancer</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
