				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Pinzarn has a good summary except the bard part
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Pinzarn wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">
<br />
Swarm kiting:  Bards used to do this until it was recently nerfed.  They would gather many, many mobs and run in cirlces playing their AE songs.  The mobs would be in range of the song but out of melee range.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
The nerfed kiting by bards is AE kiting.  The description is accurate
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Pinzarn wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">
<br />
Charm kiting:  Another bard style of kiting where you pull like four mobs.  You charm one of the mobs and the other three will beat it almost to death.  You break charm and dot the mob to death, then charm another one and repeat.  The cast time of the charm spell make this less feasible for the casting charm classes.
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
Charm kiting is known as swarm kiting in bard circles.  You use much more than 4 mobs at a time.  You use as many as you can get.  The more mobs the more damage your "pet" will take so the faster it will die.  It helps to have an instant invis spell for this so you can break charm on demand.  This was also nerfed in omens so that the highest level bard charms have low range, you have to be in melee range to charm now.  But all charms before the omens charm are still the old way with longer range.
<br />

<br />
All bard solo methods take advantage of the fact that they can cast while running.  And that bards are the fastest land mammal in EQ.<br />_________________<br />Arlania Deathkissed - necro 65
<br />
Tholuxe Paells
<br />
Chaotic Balance</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
