			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Charm tanking is whether you play a bard or necro. One charmed mob on another mob. The point is you either want the charmed mob to win  significantly or have both the charmed and uncharmed mobs hp drop to zero at the same point, break charm and get two kills at once.  There are a few invis items that can be used to break charm, notably goblin ghazugi ring and circlet of shadow that provide instant invis. Annuling magic on a charmed mob will get rid of charm as well if the charm buff is in the first slot of the mobs buffs. The benefit of using an instant item is that you can time when charm breaks much more accurately and closer to 0% hp. Also using an item to break charm means there's no recast delay before casting a spell immediately after breaking charm.
<br />

<br />
Swarm kiting really requires social mobs. I tend to take 10-20 mobs at once charm one and let the other mobs beat the charmed mob down. when the charmed mob is down to 5-10% hp then you can break charm with an invis or annul and kill it. Repeat as necessary.
<br />

<br />
AE kiting has been nerfed. It was not a good method for factioning due to the lack of places and types of mobs you could AE kite in. When you're so close to 20-30 mobs for 10-20 minutes at a time plus the 5 minutes it takes to gather mobs, one server hic-up often means instant death or a long process of regening hp (while the 20-30 mobs are regening their hp). You needed a flat, open, fairly sizable area, with a lot of common type of social mobs, to area kite with large risk to yourself during the gathering of mobs as well as during the AE'ing portion, and this assuming that no one else is in a nearby camp.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=490383" target="_blank" class="postlink">Kelter Skelter
<br />
da neckRomancer</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
