			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Just a minor point:
<br />

<br />
There are two kinds of Area of Effect (AoE) spells.  Point Blank AoE (pbAoE) like the Word line and Targeted AoE (AoE) like Infectious Cloud.
<br />

<br />
pbAoE effects an unlimited number of MOBs around you.
<br />

<br />
AoE effects the target and up to 3 nearby MOBs.
<br />

<br />
I believe pbAoE spells have a purple spell gem, while AoE have a green.
<br />

<br />
So simplified: Quad kiting Druids and Wizards manipulate MOBs into small spaces and AoE snare them, then run ahead of them pausing to zap them using targetted AoE spells. This is limited to four MOBs at time that they can snare and hurt.  The fifth would run full speed and use them like a drunk prison guard.
<br />

<br />
Necros do not have a targeted AoE snare (or targetted AoE nukes).  You can agro kite more than one MOB at a time, but in effect these are independent activies and your most mana effective DoT, your pet, can only attack one at a time.<br />_________________<br /><img src="http://www.obsessionmatrix.com/felicite_sig.jpg" border="0" />
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=809863" target="_blank" class="postlink">Felicite Belbold`Oloth</a> - <a href="http://p208.ezboard.com/bgiftofdarkness" target="_blank" class="postlink">Gift of Darkness</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
