			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">re: LDoN post-paci -- I've pet pulled entire LDoN dungeons when an add would equal death (ranger tank and beastlord healer).  Time-consuming but doable.  For times when you have a charm pet, I would just send the crypt creeper in and do your CC around it, all the while praying like hell that there is no dispeller in the room.
<br />

<br />
re: charm tanking -- Method three:  sic your charm pets against something that'll chew them up, mez damage doer when pet gets very low, break charm and kill ex-pet.  Also known as the "oh, shit, a deep red wasn't supposed to spawn yet" method.  Too mana-intensive for the xp return, not a good method.
<br />

<br />
re: swarm kiting -- This is also practiced by some suicidal enchanters.  In theory, a necro could do the same by damaging his ex-pet, then FDing the instant it dies to escape the wrath of the swarm, but then the swarm would scatter.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
